        <mxCell id="tNesn0oDd3n9oDSuALlg-33" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;FPGA GPU&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Architecture of the fixed-function GPU.&lt;br&gt;Due to memory constraints on the Basys3, the graphics pipeline processes a smaller image than actually displayed on screen.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The blue part is responsible for communicating with the CPU and runs at 100MHz. In the green part happens the actual graphics processing. This logic is clocked at half of the VGA pixel frequency. The orange part acts as display engine and generates timings and sync signals after upscaling the framebuffer by a factor of 2.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="210" width="400" x="470" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
